title: Foley High School
text: Foley High School is in <a href="Foley%2C%20Alabama">Foley, Alabama</a> and is part of the <a href="Baldwin%20County%20Public%20Schools">Baldwin County Public Schools</a> System. Foley High School has its own <a href="American%20football">American football</a>, <a href="archery">archery</a>, <a href="Cross%20country%20running">cross-country</a>, <a href="baseball">baseball</a>, <a href="cheerleading">cheerleading</a>, women's/men's <a href="soccer">soccer</a>, <a href="softball">softball</a>, and women's/men's <a href="basketball">basketball</a> teams. Along with this, there are also men's/women's <a href="track%20and%20field">track</a>, men's/women's <a href="golf">golf</a>, men's/women's <a href="tennis">tennis</a>, men's/women's <a href="wrestling">wrestling</a> , men's <a href="Swimming%20%28sport%29">swim team</a>, and <a href="volleyball">volleyball</a> teams. The school is well known for its marching and concert band, "The Mighty Band from Lion Land," which has won a <a href="Grammy">Grammy</a>. The band has been winning superior ratings at competitions in the <a href="United%20States">United States</a> since the 1970s and has performed at the <a href="Saint%20Patrick%27s%20Day%20in%20the%20United%20States%23Chicago%2C%20Illinois">Saint Patrick's Day Parade</a> in <a href="Chicago">Chicago</a>, the <a href="Daytona%20500">Daytona 500</a> race, the <a href="Fiesta%20Bowl">Fiesta Bowl</a> parade, and many more places over its long history.
